title: Warming Plate And Cover, 1986-61-7-a,b, ca. 1805
description: Two-part, round; with dish-shaped upper part and shallow circular lower part with straight sides; two loop handles opposite sides; diamond-shaped shield on side; interior of base and bottom of top tinned.
inscribed: Coat-of-arms engraved on side: diamond-shaped, with three shells horizon- tally across the top half and a shield below.
